description:
The video starts with a white background with a 3D rectangle on the left and a 3D circle on the right. The rectangle is yellow on top fading to green on the bottom. The circle is a wireframe. The shapes morph into a 2D rectangle and circle. The rectangle is now yellow on top fading to green on the bottom. The circle is now blue on the left fading to red on the right. The shapes move towards each other until they are side by side, separated by a forward slash.

The scene cuts to a large auditorium with a stage. On the stage is a large screen with the Google I/O logo. A man in a dark gray button-down shirt, blue jeans, and gray sneakers walks across the stage.

The scene cuts to the man standing in front of a blue and white background. He is smiling and has his hands clasped in front of him.

Man: "At Google, we are fully in our Gemini era."

The scene cuts back to the man on stage. The screen behind him now reads "Gemini" in blue text at the top. Below it are the logos for Google, Gmail, Android, Chrome, and YouTube.

The scene cuts back to the man in front of the blue and white background.

Man: "Today, all of our 2 billion user products use Gemini."

The scene cuts back to the man on stage. The screen behind him now reads "Gemini 1.5 Pro available today in Workspace Labs".

The scene cuts back to the man in front of the blue and white background.

Man: "Gemini 1.5 Pro is available today in Workspace Labs. Let's see how this comes to life with Google Workspace."

The scene cuts back to the man on stage. The screen behind him now reads "Google Workspace" with icons for various Google apps surrounding the text.

Man: "People are always searching their emails in Gmail."

The scene cuts back to the man in front of the blue and white background.

The scene cuts back to the man on stage. The screen behind him now shows the Gmail logo.

The scene cuts to a computer screen showing a Gmail inbox. The inbox contains several emails, one of which is highlighted. The highlighted email is from "Maywood Park Elementary School" and has the subject line "Field trip to Philadelphia needs a consent form signed by May 22, 2024". On the right side of the screen is a sidebar titled "Gemini" with a profile picture of a woman and the text "Catch me up on emails from Maywood Park Elementary Sc".

Man: "We are working to make it much more powerful with Gemini. Now, you can ask Gemini to summarize all recent emails from the school. Maybe you were traveling this week and you couldn't make the PTA meeting."

The scene cuts to the computer screen. The Gmail sidebar now shows a summary of recent emails from Maywood Park Elementary School. The summary includes the following bullet points:

* Field trip to Philadelphia needs a consent form signed by May 22, 2024
* Staff Appreciation Week is happening from May 20-May 24
* All requests for class placements must be made by June 1
* The PTA had its monthly meeting

The last bullet point is highlighted.

The scene cuts to the computer screen. The main window now shows an email from Gloria Hill with the subject line "[Recap] PTA Meeting - May 13". The email contains a link to a recording of the PTA meeting.

The scene cuts to the computer screen. The main window now shows a video player with a video titled "MPES PTA Meeting - May 13, 2024". The video shows a man and a woman in a video call. The man is wearing glasses and a black shirt. The woman has blonde hair and is wearing a blue shirt. The video is paused at the beginning. The Gemini sidebar is visible on the right side of the screen.

Man: "The recording of the meeting is an hour long. If it's from Google Meet, you can ask Gemini to give you the highlights."

The scene cuts to the computer screen. The Gemini sidebar now shows a chat window with the message "what are the main points of this meeting?".

The scene cuts to the computer screen. The Gemini sidebar now shows a chat window with the message "Sure, here is what was discussed:" followed by a bulleted list of the main points of the PTA meeting.

The scene cuts to a white background with a grid pattern. A pink and blue gradient square moves diagonally upwards from the bottom left corner to the top right corner.

The scene cuts back to the man in front of the blue and white background.

Man: "People love using Photos to search across their life."

The scene cuts back to the man on stage. The screen behind him now shows a grid of images.

Man: "With Gemini, we're making that a whole lot easier. And Ask Photos can also help you search your memories in a deeper way. For example, you might be reminiscing-"

The video ends.

**Detailed Descriptions of Subjects:**

**Man on Stage:**
* Appearance: Dark gray button-down shirt, blue jeans, gray sneakers, short black hair, glasses, goatee
* Emotion: Smiling, enthusiastic
* Actions: Walking across the stage, talking, gesturing with his hands

**Woman in Google Meet Video:**
* Appearance: Blonde hair, blue shirt
* Emotion: Neutral
* Actions: Visible in the video call but not speaking

**Man in Google Meet Video:**
* Appearance: Glasses, black shirt
* Emotion: Neutral
* Actions: Visible in the video call but not speaking

The video starts with a man standing on a stage in front of a large screen. The screen displays four photos of a young girl, presumably his daughter Lucia. He begins talking about using Google Photos to track his daughter Lucia's early milestones. He gives an example of asking Google Photos to "show me how Lucia's swimming has progressed". The screen then transitions to show a phone screen with the same question typed in the Google Photos app. The screen then transitions again to show a rapid slideshow of photos of Lucia swimming. The photos are shown in a diagonal stack, scrolling from bottom to top. The photos transition to a summary of six photos of Lucia swimming. The screen then transitions back to the phone screen, this time showing the summary of photos with a text description below. The man then continues talking, explaining that Google built Gemini to be multimodal from the ground up. The screen behind him transitions to show a blue background with four icons, representing text, images, video, and audio. He explains that it's one model with all the modalities built in. The man continues, explaining that they have been gradually rolling out Gemini 1.5 Pro with long context in preview over the last few months. The screen behind him transitions to show a grid of the same four icons from before, this time in blue and white. The grid then transitions to show a large "2M" in the center, with the word "tokens" below and "Gemini 1.5 Pro" above. The man continues, stating that today they are expanding the context window to 2 million tokens. The audience begins clapping and cheering. The screen transitions to black. The man continues speaking, stating that so far they have talked about two technical advances: multimodality and long context. The screen behind him transitions to show the words "Multimodality" and "Long Context" on the left and right side of the screen, respectively. An icon is displayed next to each word. He explains that each is powerful on its own, but together they unlock deeper capabilities and more intelligence. The man concludes by asking "What if we could go even further?". 

The video features one subject:

The subject is a man with short, dark hair, a short beard and mustache, and is wearing glasses. He is wearing a gray button-up shirt with the sleeves rolled up to his elbows. He is standing on a stage in front of a large screen. He appears to be giving a presentation about Google's new AI model, Gemini. He is smiling and appears to be enthusiastic about the topic. He speaks with his hands, using them to emphasize his points.

The video starts with Sundar Pichai, CEO of Google, talking about the opportunities of AI agents. He describes them as intelligent systems that show reasoning, planning, and memory. He says they are able to think multiple steps ahead, work across software and systems, all to get something done on your behalf, and most importantly, under your supervision.

The video then cuts to a man with glasses and a blue sweater, who introduces himself as the speaker for today. He says that they have some exciting new progress to share about the future of AI assistance that they are calling Project Astra. He explains that they have wanted to build a universal AI agent that can be truly helpful in everyday life. He then introduces a video of their prototype, which he says has two parts, each part was captured in a single take in real-time.

The video then cuts to a person holding a smartphone, showing a video call with a person on the other side. The person on the call asks "What does that part of the code do?". A voice, identified as Gemini, responds with "This code defines encryption and decryption functions." Gemini continues, "It seems to use AES-CBC encryption to encode and decode data based on a key and an initialization vector (IV)."

**Detailed descriptions of each subject:**

**Sundar Pichai:**
* **Appearance:** Wears a gray button-down shirt, glasses, and has short, dark hair and a beard.
* **Emotion:** Appears calm and collected, speaking in a clear and concise manner.
* **Actions:** Stands still with his hands clasped in front of him.

**Second Speaker:**
* **Appearance:** Wears a blue sweater and glasses, and has short, dark hair and a beard.
* **Emotion:** Appears enthusiastic and passionate about the project.
* **Actions:** Uses hand gestures while speaking.

**Person on Video Call:**
* **Appearance:** Only their hands are visible, holding a smartphone.
* **Emotion:** Not discernible.
* **Actions:** Holds the phone steady, showing the video call and code.

**Gemini (voice only):**
* **Appearance:** Not applicable.
* **Emotion:** Speaks in a neutral tone.
* **Actions:** Not applicable.

The video starts with a person holding a phone in their hands. The phone is in a video call and the person is showing the other person on the call the room around them. The person asks "Do you remember where you saw my glasses?". The other person on the call, named Gemini, responds "Yes, I do. Your glasses were on the desk near a red apple.". The person holding the phone then finds their glasses on the desk next to a red apple.
The video then cuts to a different person petting a dog. The person asks "Uh give me a band name for this duo.". The person is holding a stuffed tiger toy next to the dog. Gemini responds "Golden Stripes.". The person laughs and says "Nice. Thanks Gemini.".
The video then cuts to a man in a blue sweater standing in front of a blue and white background. He says "Today, we're introducing Gemini 1.5 Flash.".
The video then cuts to the same man standing on a stage in front of a large screen. The screen says "Gemini 1.5 Flash" on it. The man says "Flash is a lighter-weight model compared to Pro. It's designed to be fast and cost-efficient to serve at scale, while still featuring multi-modal reasoning capabilities and breakthrough long context.".
The video then cuts back to the man in front of the blue and white background. He says "There's one more area I'm really excited to share with you. Our teams have made some incredible progress in generative video.".
The video then cuts back to the man on the stage. He says "Today, I'm excited to announce our newest, most capable generative video model called...". The screen behind him changes to show a video of a city at night. The man continues "Veo.".
The video then cuts to a black screen with the word "Veo" in the center. Six smaller videos are arranged around the word, showing various scenes: a city street at night, a mountain lake, a cityscape at night, a satellite in space, a close-up of an alpaca's face, and an underwater shot of a coral reef. The words "Unedited raw output" are displayed below the videos.

Detailed descriptions of the subjects:

**First part:**
* **Person 1:** This person is not visible in the video, we only see their hands and forearms. They have light skin and are wearing a white long-sleeved shirt. They are holding a phone in their hands and are using it to show the other person on the call the room around them. They are looking for their glasses and ask Gemini for help finding them.
* **Gemini:** This person is also not visible in the video, we only hear their voice. They are able to remember where the first person saw their glasses and provide accurate directions to help them find them.
* **Glasses:** The glasses are black-framed with clear lenses. They are found on a desk next to a red apple.
* **Red apple:** The apple is red and shiny. It is sitting on a desk next to a pair of glasses.

**Second part:**
* **Person 2:** This person is also not visible in the video, we only see their hands and forearms. They have light skin and are petting a dog. They are holding a stuffed tiger toy in one hand and petting the dog with the other. They ask Gemini for a band name for the dog and the tiger toy.
* **Dog:** The dog is a golden retriever. It is sitting down and looking at the camera. It has a white patch of fur on its chest. The dog appears calm and happy to be petted.
* **Stuffed tiger toy:** The toy is a small, orange and black striped tiger. It is being held in the person's hand.

**Third part:**
* **Man on stage:** The man is light-skinned and has short, dark hair and a short beard. He is wearing glasses with blue arms and a blue long-sleeved sweater. He appears to be excited and passionate about the product he is presenting. He speaks clearly and confidently.

The video showcases the capabilities of Google's AI, Gemini, in various tasks like visual memory, creative suggestions, and generative video creation. It highlights the advancements in AI technology and its potential applications in different fields.

The video starts with a collage of images, including a cityscape at night, a mountain lake, a cityscape during the day, a person holding a camera, and an alpaca. The title "Veo" is displayed in the center of the collage. The text "Unedited raw output" is displayed below the collage.

Next, a smartphone is shown with text on the screen that reads "Prompt: A fast-tracking shot through a bustling dystopian sprawl with bright neon signs, flying cars and mist, night, lens flare, volumetric lighting". The video then transitions to a fast-tracking shot through a bustling dystopian sprawl with bright neon signs, flying cars, and mist at night. The shot includes lens flare and volumetric lighting.

The video then cuts to a large crowd of people sitting in an auditorium. They are clapping their hands and smiling. The video then cuts to a man with dark hair and a short beard standing on a stage in front of a large screen. He is wearing a gray shirt and has his hands clasped in front of him. He is speaking to the audience. The screen behind him is blank.

The man says, "For 25 years, we have invested in world-class technical infrastructure. Today, we are excited to announce the sixth generation of TPUs called Trillium."

The video then cuts to a different man with dark hair and a short beard standing on a stage in front of a large screen. He is wearing a gray shirt and blue jeans. The screen behind him shows a picture of a computer chip and the text "Trillium 6th generation TPUs". The man is speaking to an audience that is sitting in front of him.

The man on the stage says, "Trillium delivers a 4.7x improvement in compute performance per chip over the previous generation."

The video then cuts back to the first man. The screen behind him now shows the text "Google Search Generative AI at the scale of human curiosity".

The man says, "Google Search is Generative AI at the scale of human curiosity, and it's our most exciting chapter of Search yet."

The video then cuts back to the crowd of people in the auditorium. They are clapping their hands and smiling. The video then cuts to a woman with short, curly brown hair standing on a stage in front of a large screen. She is wearing a black blazer over a purple shirt. The screen behind her is blank.

The woman says, "All the advancements you'll see today are made possible by a new Gemini model customized for Google Search. But what really sets this apart is our three unique strengths. This is Search in the Gemini era. By the end of the year, AI overviews will come to over a billion people. We're making AI overviews even more helpful for your most..."

The video ends with the woman's speech unfinished.

**Detailed Descriptions of Subjects:**

**Subject 1: First Man**
* Appearance: Dark hair, short beard, wearing a gray shirt
* Emotion: Excited, enthusiastic
* Actions: Speaking to an audience, gesturing with his hands

**Subject 2: Second Man**
* Appearance: Dark hair, short beard, wearing a gray shirt and blue jeans
* Emotion: Neutral, informative
* Actions: Speaking to an audience

* Appearance: Short, curly brown hair, wearing a black blazer over a purple shirt
* Emotion: Confident, enthusiastic
* Actions: Speaking to an audience, gesturing with her hands

**Other Subjects:**

* Crowd: Large group of people, diverse in appearance, clapping, smiling
* Screen: Large screen behind the speakers, displaying text and images

The video starts with a woman with short curly brown hair, wearing a purple shirt and a black blazer, standing in front of a white wall with a blue stripe at the top. She is looking at the camera and talking about complex questions.

**Woman 1:** "...complex questions."

The video then cuts to a white screen with a Google search bar in the center. The search bar is populated with the following text: "Find the best yoga or pilates studios in Boston and show details on their intro offers and walking time from beacon hill".

The video then cuts to a white smartphone with a Google search page open. The search bar at the top of the screen shows the same text as the previous screen. Below the search bar, there are several lines of text that say "Generating...", "Searching the web...", "Finding places...", and "Putting it all together...".

The video then cuts back to the woman in the purple shirt and black blazer. She is now standing on a stage in front of a large screen. The screen is black with a smaller screen inside of it. The smaller screen is showing a video of a man in a white shirt bending over.

**Woman 1:** "The types that are really more like 10 questions in one."

The video then cuts back to the smartphone. The screen now shows a list of four yoga and pilates studios in Boston. Each listing includes the studio's name, rating, walking time from Beacon Hill, and intro offer.

**Woman 1:** "You can ask your entire question with all its sub-questions and get an AI overview in seconds."

The video then cuts back to the woman on stage. She is smiling and looking at the camera.

**Woman 1:** "I'm really excited to share that soon you'll be able to ask questions with video."

The video then cuts to a split screen. On the left side of the screen, a woman with black hair wearing a denim jacket is standing behind a turntable. She is holding a smartphone in her right hand and talking. On the right side of the screen, the smartphone is shown in more detail. The screen of the phone is showing a video of the turntable and the woman's hand. The text "Speak now to ask about this video" is displayed at the bottom of the screen.

**Woman 1:** "Why will this not stay in place?"

The video then cuts back to the smartphone. The screen now shows a Google search page with the text "Why will this not stay in place" in the search bar. Below the search bar, there is a list of search results.

The video then cuts back to the woman with the black hair. She is still standing behind the turntable and talking.

**Woman 2:** "And in near instant, Google gives me an AI overview."

The video then cuts to a woman with long black hair wearing a pink blazer and blue jeans. She is standing in front of a white wall with a blue stripe at the top. She is looking at the camera and talking.

**Woman 3:** "Since last May, we've been hard at work making Gemini for Workspace even more helpful for businesses and consumers across the world."

The video then cuts to the woman on stage. The screen behind her now shows the Google Workspace logo.

The video then cuts back to the woman on stage. The screen behind her now shows a blurred image of a mobile phone with text messages.

The video then cuts to a woman with long black hair wearing a beige blazer and a white shirt. She is standing in front of a white wall with a blue stripe at the top. She is looking at the camera and talking.

The video begins with a woman standing on a stage in front of a large screen. She is wearing a beige blazer and black pants. She is smiling and appears to be enthusiastic.

**Woman:** AI is delivering our most intelligent AI experience. We're rolling out a new feature that lets you customize it for your own needs and create personal experts on any topic you want. We're calling these Gems. They're really simple to set up, just tap to create a Gem, write your instructions once, and come back whenever you need it. Starting today, Gemini Advanced subscribers get access to Gemini 1.5 Pro with 1 million tokens. That is the longest context window of any chatbot in the world. You can upload a PDF up to 1,500 pages long or multiple files to get insights across a project.

(The audience applauds)

**Woman:** Now, we all know that chatbots can give you ideas for your next vacation, but there's a lot more that goes into planning a great trip. It requires reasoning that considers space-time logistics and the intelligence...

The video ends.

**Subject Descriptions:**

**Woman:**
* Appearance: Asian woman with long, dark hair. She is wearing a beige blazer over a white shirt, black pants, and black shoes.
* Emotion: She appears to be enthusiastic and passionate about the product she is presenting. She smiles throughout the video and speaks with energy.
* Actions: She stands on a stage and gestures with her hands as she speaks. She does not move around the stage much.

**Other:**
* The stage is circular and made of light-colored wood.
* The screen behind the woman is large and black. It displays various graphics and text throughout the video.
* The audience is large and diverse. They are seated in rows of chairs facing the stage. They applaud at one point during the video.

The video starts with a woman standing on a stage in front of a large screen. The screen displays five images: a location pin icon, a cityscape, an airplane icon, a sunset over water, and a building.

The woman says: "to prioritize and make decisions. That reasoning and intelligence all come together in the new trip planning experience in Gemini Advanced."

The video then cuts to a man with a beard and a black hoodie standing in front of a blue and white background. He says: "We've embarked on a multi-year journey to reimagine Android with AI at the core."

The video cuts back to the stage, where a different man is now standing behind a podium. A large screen behind him displays a message that reads "Good morning. Type, talk, or share a photo."

The man behind the podium says: "Now, we're making Gemini context aware, so it can anticipate what you're trying to do and provide more helpful suggestions in the moment. Let me show you how this works. So, my friend Pete is asking me if I want to play pickleball this weekend, but I'm new to this pickleball thing, and I can bring up Gemini to help with that. Gemini knows I'm looking at a video, so it proactively shows me an ask this video chip. So let me tap on that, and now I can ask specific questions about the video. So for example, uh, what is the two bounce rule? So give it a moment, and there. I get a nice, distinct answer."

The video then shows a close-up of the man's phone screen. The screen displays a YouTube video titled "How to Play Pickleball (THE BASICS)." A chat box at the bottom of the screen shows the man's question, "what is the two bounce rule," and Gemini's response, "According to the video, the two bounce rule is standard to serving in pickleball. After the serving drive is struck, the ball must bounce once on the returner's side then bounce once more on the server's side before you can start volleying. You can volley the ball from anywhere on the court except for from the kitchen."

The video cuts back to the man, who says: "Starting with Pixel later this year, we'll be expanding."

The video is about Google's new AI technology. It features two speakers on a stage at a Google event.

The first speaker announces the Gemini Nano model with multimodality, which allows phones to understand the world through text, sights, sounds, and spoken language.

The second speaker discusses Gemma, a family of open models crucial for driving AI innovation and responsibility. He announces the release of PaLiGemma, their first vision language open model, and Gemma 2, the next generation of Gemma, which will be available in June with a new 27 billion parameter model. He concludes by stating that building AI responsibly means both addressing the risks and maximizing the benefits.

**Speaker 1:**

* **Appearance:** A man with short brown hair and a light beard. He is wearing a brown long-sleeved shirt and dark blue jeans. He has a smartwatch on his left wrist and a ring on his left ring finger.
* **Emotion:** He appears enthusiastic and passionate about the technology he is presenting.
* **Actions:** He is standing on a stage, gesturing with his hands as he speaks.
* **Words:** "Imagine what's possible with our latest model, Gemini Nano with multimodality. This means your phone can understand the world the way you understand it. So not just through text input, but also through sights, sounds, and spoken language."

**Speaker 2:**

* **Appearance:** A man with short blonde hair and glasses. He is wearing a dark gray hoodie and dark blue jeans.
* **Emotion:** He appears excited and proud to announce the new AI models.
* **Actions:** He is standing on a stage, clapping his hands together and gesturing as he speaks.
* **Words:** "Now, let's shift gears and talk about Gemma, our family of open models which are crucial for driving AI innovation and responsibility. Today's newest member, PaLiGemma, our first vision language open model and it's available right now. I'm also excited to announce that we have Gemma 2 coming. It's the next generation of Gemma and it will be available in June. So in a few weeks, we'll be adding a new 27 billion parameter model to Gemma 2."

**Other:**

* The video shows a large screen behind the speakers, displaying visuals related to the topics being discussed.
* The audience is visible in some shots, appearing engaged and applauding the announcements.
* The stage has a minimalist design with a wooden podium and Google's signature colorful branding.

The video starts with a man giving a presentation on a stage in front of a large audience. The stage has a large screen behind it. The screen displays the words "Building AI responsibly".

The video then cuts to the man standing in front of a blue and white background. He is talking about how Google is improving its AI models.

The man on the stage is wearing a light brown overshirt over a black shirt and black pants. He is bald and has a short beard. He is wearing glasses and has a microphone clipped to his shirt. He appears to be passionate about the topic he is presenting.

The man says: "for people and society. We're improving our models with an industry standard practice called red teaming, in which we test our own models and try to break them to identify weaknesses. I'm excited to introduce LearnAlam, our new family of models based on Gemini and fine-tuned for learning. Another example is a new feature in YouTube that uses LearnAlam to make educational videos more interactive, allowing you to ask a clarifying question, get a helpful explanation, or take a quiz."

As he speaks, the screen behind him changes to display the words "Red Teaming" and then "LearnLM". A video then plays on the screen showing a phone with an interactive quiz about a coding tutorial video.

The video then cuts to a different man standing in front of the same blue and white background. This man is wearing a gray button-down shirt. He is also wearing glasses and has a microphone clipped to his shirt. He has short, dark hair and a short beard. He is smiling and appears to be pleased with the progress that has been made.

The second man says: "All of this shows the important progress we have made as we take a bold and responsible approach to making AI helpful for everyone. To everyone here in Shoreline and the millions more watching around the world, here's to the possibilities ahead and creating them together. Thank you."

The video then cuts back to the stage, where the second man is now standing. He waves to the audience as they applaud. The video ends with a shot of the Google logo.
